- A dataset download represents an instance where a user has accessed and downloaded data related to a particular ecosystem;
- The statistics (total, average, maximum, and minimum downloads) provide insights into the popularity and usage patterns of datasets associated with each ecosystem.

- "Recently updated" refers to ecosystems updated within the last year;
- "Largest" refers to ecosystems with a size greater than 100 square kilometers;
- "Dataset density" is calculated as the number of datasets associated with the ecosystem divided by the total number of ecosystems.

- "flourishing growth of dataset downloads" refers to the highest number of downloads in the last year;
- "top 5 ecosystems" means the ecosystems with the highest download counts;
- "names of the datasets and reports" are the specific identifiers for the datasets and reports linked to the ecosystems.

