- "datasets" are collections of data related to these ecosystems;
- "dataset_downloads" track how many times each dataset has been accessed or downloaded.

sql:
SELECT dataset_id, download_date
FROM dataset_downloads
ORDER BY download_date DESC;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS number_of_downloads
FROM dataset_downloads
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT dataset_id, COUNT(*) AS download_count
FROM dataset_downloads
GROUP BY dataset_id;

